    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Micah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Priests who teach for hire and prophets who divine for money bring a curse upon the people.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And I said, Hear, I pray you, O heads of Jacob, and ye princes of the house of Israel; Is it not for you to know judgment?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Who hate the good, and love the evil; who pluck off their skin from off them, and their flesh from off their bones;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who also eat the flesh of my people, and flay their skin from off them; and they break their bones, and chop them in pieces, as for the pot, and as flesh within the caldron.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then shall they cry unto the Lord, but he will not hear them: he will even hide his face from them at that time, as they have behaved themselves ill in their doings.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 11:24 (23\u201325). TG\u00a0God, Access to.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thus saith the Lord concerning the prophets that make my people err, that bite with their teeth, and cry, Peace; and he that putteth not into their mouths, they even prepare war against him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Prophets.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 11:35 (34\u201336); D&C 121:38.",
                        "start": 174,
                        "end": 177
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore night shall be unto you, that ye shall not have a vision; and it shall be dark unto you, that ye shall not divine; and the sun shall go down over the prophets, and the day shall be dark over them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 38:11 (11\u201312); 112:23; Moses 7:61 (61\u201362).",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 13:23.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 8:9.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 136
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 1:17 (13\u201317).",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 168
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then shall the seers be ashamed, and the diviners confounded: yea, they shall all cover their lips; for there is no answer of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 13:4; 2\u00a0Ne. 6:13 (7, 13); D&C 90:17.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Superstitions.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 29:10.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But truly I am full of power by the spirit of the Lord, and of judgment, and of might, to declare unto Jacob his transgression, and to Israel his sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Power of.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of; Holy Ghost, Mission of.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 24:9 (7\u20139); Hel. 13:26.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 126
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hear this, I pray you, ye heads of the house of Jacob, and princes of the house of Israel, that abhor judgment, and pervert all equity.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They build up Zion with blood, and Jerusalem with iniquity.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The heads thereof judge for reward, and the priests thereof teach for hire, and the prophets thereof divine for money: yet will they lean upon the Lord, and say, Is not the Lord among us? none evil can come upon us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Israel; False Prophets.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priestcraft.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 117
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 162,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore shall Zion for your sake be plowed as a field, and Jerusalem shall become heaps, and the mountain of the house as the high places of the forest.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 12:3.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 26:18.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 3:8.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 1:7.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the temple.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
